Title: Part-Time Youth Developer  &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Location: Daly City, Bayshore and Lomita Park Sites, (Depending on Club Needs)&amp;nbsp;Reports To: Area DirectorSalary: $16hr + (DOE) &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;About the Mid-Peninsula Boys & Girls Club (MPBGC)&amp;nbsp;The Mid-Peninsula Boys & Girls Club is a non-profit organization that has served youth between the ages of 5 and 19 years since 1955. We are part of a national movement that began in 1860 and now serves over 4.8 million youth in over 4,000 Boys & Girls Clubs across the country. As part of our mission, we provide our members with a wide array of educational, recreational and social activities in a safe and structured environment during after-school hours.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We believe our success is achieved through our talented and motivated staff members. Our staff is a diverse group of people: some are in college, some are coaches, while others have family with children of their own. Whether a staff member is full-time, part-time, or seasonal, everyone plays a key role in our youths’ growth and achievements in all facets of life. Not to mention all the lifetime memories with our kids!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   Check us out at: https://www.midpenbgc.org/   Once you are here, you will be able to:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;  - Help inspire and positively impact the lives of the youth we serve.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Grow hands on experience building community within your respective youth group and provide fun and engaging programs for our kids.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Grow skills in project-based learning, event coordination, and leadership skills.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Receive professional development trainings, online learnings, and specialized certifications to ensure your own personal and professional growth.&amp;nbsp;   
   What does BGC offer you?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;  - Part Time shift hours:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
	Monday to Friday (Except Wed.):&amp;nbsp;2:00pm – 6:30pm&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;	Wednesdays 12:30pm - 6:30pm&amp;nbsp;(Varies per site)   - Creative work environment.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Professional and Personal Development.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
  - Periodic job-related perks such as attending professional sporting events, movies, and outdoor activities.&amp;nbsp;   
   This role is ideal for someone with the following traits:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;  - Strong oral and written communication skills.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Responsible human beings who care for the well being of themselves and others.&amp;nbsp;   
  - &amp;nbsp;Interest/ability to partner with teammates in shared efforts to provide youth supervision and group/program management.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
  - Community minded and wants to see others succeed.    
  - &amp;nbsp;High level of comfort having fun with the kids! We take our work seriously but not ourselves.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
  - Embraces being a child at heart, being silly highly encouraged!&amp;nbsp;   
   ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS&amp;nbsp;Speaking Spanish is a plus.&amp;nbsp;Must have valid California Driver’s License, proof of auto liability insurance and a good driving record. May be required to drive 9 passenger van. Must pass background check and provide TB test clearance.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS/WORK ENVIRONMENT&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;This position may require the ability to lift 40lbs.&amp;nbsp;The position may entail long periods of standing and/or walking.&amp;nbsp;There may be periods of high levels of ambient noise.&amp;nbsp;This position may include both indoor and outdoor environmental conditions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;DISCLAIMER&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The information presented indicates the general nature and level of work expected of employees in this classification. It is not designed to contain, nor to be interpreted as, a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities, qualifications and objectives required of employees assigned to this job.
